        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There should be an easy method for retrieving the schema and table name from a Zend_Db_Table instance. It should be a string, properly formatted with quotes, for quick insertion into Zend_Db_Select and raw SQL queries. I was thinking this method might be called getSchemaName() \u2014 unless someone can think of something more concise?\n\nZend_Db_Table_Abstract::__toString() should proxy this method to make things even more fluent."
